prabhat goyal that s not true  a tesla uses its own proprietary fluids to cool and manage the battery and electric motors  which will have to be replaced down the line  another problem is that nobody can sell parts for a tesla since they are proprietary  which means your forced to bring it directly to tesla with a normal but expensive markup  in fact  a tesla may be more hassle than a normal car because the charging stations are far more sparse than regular gas or petrol stations  even a non enthusiast can appreciate a reliable and robust car  but tesla s are still patchy in terms of reliability even though they are getting better  another problem is that you can t use universal parts on a tesla  since everything is patented and proprietary  if you need to replace a battery module in toyota prius you are looking at several thousand dollars  but that s a prius  which has universal parts since the patent expired  it s true that tesla will most likely fix these issues in the future but we don t know how soon  tesla s may have an electric pt but they still require hydraulic fluid for the brakes and coolant for the radiators  the tesla used industry standard disc brakes with that comes replacing pads and rotors  another problem is that tesla s depreciate like a heavy rock  you can pick up a 2016 anything for almost 10 or 15 thousand below the msrp  the internal combustion car has been refined and honed for almost 120 years as opposed to electric cars which have only popped up in the last 20 years  lastly  most of the time it takes a decent chunk of time to charge a tesla  not sure how much  but that s a bit inconvenient and is  the nature of electric powered anything  much less a full blown car

fun to drive  i had the option of getting the 435i but i actually liked the 428i better as it just felt better   it was slower  but it cornered better and did not feel as nose heavy  so my mostly tricked out 428i  would i rather have that or have this  well there is no way that this is as fun to drive   the bmw is the best handling car i have ever owned  one of my previous car was a c6 corvette  while the bmw had the tech package  the amount of tech in the bmw really is not all that impressive  i loved the full color hud with gps built in  it was fantastic since you would get on windshield directions  what lane to be in  etc  all with never looking down   but outside of that it was mostly basic stuff and it lacked many of the features that my fully loaded cts had  like dvd audio and air conditioned seats  the model 3 is not a very good looking car  but it is not horrendous  but the 428i certainly looks better  also while the bmw has a fairly bland looking interior  once you actually sit behind the wheel you realize how good it is as everything is laid out fantastically   the tesla interior however looks extremely gimmicky   as for the battery issue  whatever  i do not care if it is gas or electric  but i do like the idea of roller coaster like acceleration  the 428i has a twin turbo 4 cyclinder  and when the bmw dealer told me it was only a 4 under the hood i nearly spit in his face for insulting me by even asking me to drive it  but honestly it is a great engine  the car has a low 5s 0 60 and as mentioned earlier the car handles great because it is not too heavy   the 6cyl 435i is very nose heavy and driving the two back to back  you can tell the bmw was built around the 4 which has perfect 50 50 balance  the tesla meanwhile is not going to be handling monster  it is just too heavy   so what would i do  having never driven a tesla  well i would buy it over the 428i for a few basic reasons  the amount of tech in the tesla is just amazing   but mainly the auto pilot  that is a huge selling point to me  i love driving on empty roads  but the option of letting the car take car of the driving in traffic is fantastic and it will only get better  the 428i i had has no ability to ever do that

j and j studio the bolt is not even close to the model 3 that is in this video  this model 3 costs nearly  60 000  i am talking the base model  so the smaller battery  no glass roof  no upgraded sound system  no autopilot  etc  tesla is trying to market the model 3 as a mass market  affordable ev  however every review i see is talking about a version that is in the high  50 thousands  that is not affordable for most people  now i know that the base model is not even available yet  so it is impossible to review  however  i think that when you compare apples to apples  the bolt would compare pretty well to it  it has a slightly longer range  more spacious interior  more cargo space  with the rear seats folded flat  it does not look as good  handle as nice  or accelerate quite as quickly as the model 3  but some buyers might put more emphasis on its other features  for example i live in new england  so the base model 3 s rear wheel drive is basically a deal breaker for me  as much as i like the styling better than the bolt s  the bolt is a better winter driver  i do not think the bolt is poorly made  it is just not luxurious  i had an acura before  it is a huge step down in interior quality from my tsx  i wanted an ev though  and the bolt checked all my required boxes in a vehicle  luxury is nice  but it is not essential to me

haniho ho are you saying that it is a no brainer to add nearly  10 000 to the price of the car to get a more luxurious car with the tesla bells and whistles  sure  if you have the money to spare  but that is not the supposed point of the model 3  it is supposed to be an affordable long range ev that can compete with price wise with mass market sedans  it is targeted at people like me  i was looking for a new car  i wanted an ev  but i did not want to pay much more than i would had i gotten a top end accord or low end luxury model  something like an acura ilx  i was not going to pay  55 grand for the long range model 3  it is just too much  especially considering that i ended up purchasing my bolt  when it seemed like the new tax bill was going to eliminate the federal ev credit   the bolt was the only long range ev in my price range  and even that was at the higher end of it  i think a lot of people are in the same boat as me  they would like an ev  but they need them to be closer to that   30 000 price point in order for them to make sense financially  that is why i think a bolt vs  base model 3 would be interesting to a lot of people  those are the only two relatively affordable long range evs  i think people would like to know how they compare dollar to dollar

michael riveccio i am saying the base model 3 is the better car than the bolt for the same price  the rear panoroof is standard that makes the cabin more roomy  there is heated front seats a faster more modern infotainment   and speakers better than the standard 3 series  for cargo there is frunk trunk capacity  along with seats folded down makes it very comparable to the bolt  there is more center console storage without the gear knob  and there is a phone dock for two and a rear armrest with cupholders  the smartphone is your keyless entry  the 3 has faster acceleration and sporty handling which is more fun  along with it looking way nicer in and out   the autopilot features is likely to be free  when self driving is the norm  so it is more future proof than the bolt that does not get ota updates

aleksandr vysockij it is not about the mustang  i know it is nothing more than a loud horsepower mammoth  it is about this whole electric car thing in general  they say it is eco friendly but at the end of the day  the raw materials and the production process itself end up  consuming nature   as they call it  i am not one of those nature lover retards  the only good to the environment they do is not polluting the air in non industrial areas  but all that for what  a vehicle with no real thrill to drive  sit back and relax  where is the fun in that  where is the roar  where is the satisfaction you get when you change the gear properly  unless of course if you are some 12 y o nerd who loves futuristic things   and yes  electric vehicles are faster than gas driven  there are technical reasons behind it  no shift delays  less weight and as such  but all that aside  it takes the soul of driving out of it

that  soul  often said to be lacking in evs is highly subjective  it is exactly the lack of mechanisms the spools  the turbos that excite me about the car  like the thing s been streamlined to peak efficiency its powertrain stripped of non essentials  like a lithe ambush predator  like thunder less lightning  and the point of the ev revolution is not to avoid consumption completely and absolutely  that would be impossible and in strict violation with the universe  but to lessen it significantly  the point is not to stop polluting at all  but to lower environmental impact over the lifetime of the vehicle  start small somewhere and build up over time  the satisfaction to be found here is in uninterrupted  unadulterated  disquieting acceleration  that and a lower maintenance bill due to fewer moving parts   though your mileage may vary on that last bit

azalru elon has said repeatedly and unequivocally that the base model with no options with be the best car that you can buy for  35 000  ignoring tax incentives  that car has no lane keep assist  much less auto lane change  no android auto or car play  no adaptive cruise control  no lane departure warning  no heated seats or steering wheel  no power adjusting seats  and just over 200 miles of range  there are many  many cars that cost less than  35 000 and yet still include all of these features  with ranges of up to 700 miles  i know evs have certain inherent benefits  but the model 3 is still expensive for the features you are getting

the base model has front heated seats  autopilot live information of cars all around and ahead even in fog  apple like gui on ipad pro responsive ui that is the fastest on the market  large touchscreen that is brighter and better quality than an ipad pro  with a large back up camera that can be left on while driving  rear helicopter panoramic roof for the rear passengers  auto wipers that utilizes the camera and not an outdated rain sensor  auto charge port that lights up  deep center console storage  frunk and deep well trunk with no tunnel hump  audio system that is better than a 3 series   smartphone app that preheats the car  one of kind hvac system that is aesthetically pleasing and is more intuitive than upfront air vents  0 60 near 5 seconds  and ota updates   700 miles is pointless if you have to go on gas errands in the freezing cold and then pay for it   220 miles is more than enough for daily driving  and the supercharger network is widespread for road trips  with the tax credit you can get autopilot  and even later when selfdriving becomes norm  it might even be for free

azalru first of all  please show me one reliable source confirming heated front seats in the base model with no options  everything i have read indicates that it does not  base model does not have autopilot  i think you know this  it is an option that you have to pay significantly for  the tax credit will be expired before anyone not already on the reservation list gets a model 3  and many on the reservation list already will not get the credit  the size of the touchscreen is irrelevant  it looks cool and fancy  but it is not utilitarian  i actually happen to like physical knobs for most car controls  you can use them without looking  unlike a touchscreen  rain sensors work perfectly fine  i could not care less about the audio  but most cars in the  35 000 range can include audio upgrades  many cars have a smartphone app that can turn on the ac or heater  that is been a thing for years  the hvac system is pretty cool  but not a killer feature  again  0 60 time is irrelevant for daily drivers  i am not sure what you mean by  errands in the freezing cold and then pay for it  gas cars heat you with the wasted heat of the engine  rather than cutting a huge chunk out of your range  that is why lack of heated seats on the base model is such a big deal  look  if you think the model 3 is a bargain  go for it  i was super excited about the model 3  i got on the reservation list the day of the announcement  but i am looking at things realistically  and the value proposition just is not there  the base model with no options is nothing special  and lacks tons of important features that i can get for much cheaper  and i definitely cannot afford the  50 000  model that actually does include all the cutting edge awesome features  nor can most people

model 3 owners club posted the standard list including heated front seats  even you do not get autopilot  the autopilot display is still on  showing all the related information  everyone who has seen the screen knows this   the big touchscreen has a huge navigation map  and back up camera  and will be used for movies  completely relevant to the half million reservists with some that will get the tax credit  physical knobs and buttons are ugly just like blackberries and nokias  they do not fit with our modern tech filled lifestyles and everyday smartphones   neural vision works better than rain sensors  audio upgrades still not as good as the base model 3   very few actually and still not as good as the smartphone app from silicon valley   and only tesla can turn on climate control in a closed garage   the hvac is better than fiddling with manual air vent multiple times as you sit back  acceleration is completely relevant for highways   and noted by the whole industry advertising it   is more important than your love for buttons   gas cars turn off while you get outside and pump gas  and pay for it in inclement weather  tesla owners do not suffer this reoccurring chore    heated seats are standard on the base model 3  i find other cars that do not have the feature set of the model 3   a complete waste of money  like paying for an old flip phone for the price a modern smartphone flagship

actually  supercars are not necessarily designed to be the most drag efficient  that is for long range cars or to optimize efficiency  aka your tesla model s   the model s has the lowest drag coefficient of any other production car of around 2 3  supercars however  are designed to create downforce  as you mentioned earlier  however downforce creates quite alot of drag  thus lowering the top speed  you are correct that a 720s is much more drag efficient than 99 9  of cars  but the focus is definitely more on downforce rather than aerodynamic efficiency  to elaborate  in 1998  mclaren developed the  f1   not their f1 team  which had 610hp  down 110hp compared to the 720s  and weighed only 300lbs less  based on just those two numbers alone  some would assume the f1 s top speed is similar to that of the 720  but in 1998  mclaren was able to get their f1 to go 243mph  a record undefeated until the veyron came out in 2006  sure the extremely light weight of 2643lbs contributed to that  but the mclaren f1 is much more aerodynamically efficient compared to the 720s  and is able to achieve such a higher top speed  however  today s world of cars has top speed irrelevant  and the 720s would run circles around 99 99  of cars due to the developments in modern aero design and downforce   also mclaren s suspension is unreal
